other doctrines of the faith. It is an irradiation of the soul by the
very life of the Trinity being thus imparted to it from Him who is its
Principle; in short, to use the words of the Apostle to whom he speaks,
he is now 'partaker of Divine nature.' True, the supernatural light is
but a star as yet, since faith is seeing Divine things 'in a mirror,'
and not 'face to face'; nevertheless it is the spiritual beginning of
the final vision, for, as Aquinas says, 'to the Blessed the invisible
mission is made the very ^principle~ of their beatitude'".

